    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect type cast in RRCSetupRequest random value handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `do_RRCSetupRequest` function in the NR RRC message construction code used an implicit type cast when masking the unused bit in the InitialUE-Identity random value. This could cause data corruption or misinterpretation downstream when the RRC message is processed by the network.\n\nThe issue manifests when the UE attempts to establish an RRC connection. The network may fail to properly resolve the contention resolution identity due to the corrupted random value, leading to failed RRC setup procedures.\n\nThis fix makes the type casting explicit to prevent any potential issues with integer promotion or signed/unsigned conversion that could cause data corruption.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/MESSAGES/asn1_msg.c`: Made type casting explicit in bitwise operation for masking unused bit in InitialUE-Identity random value.\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/MESSAGES/asn1_msg.c`: Minor whitespace formatting change in `do_NR_RRCReconfigurationComplete_for_nsa` function (tabs to spaces).\n\n"
}